<body>
  <main class="wrap">
    <a class="back" href="/">
      <span aria-hidden="true">←</span><span>Back</span>
    </a>

    <h1>Cooling</h1>

    <section class="section tight" aria-label="Servings">
      <div class="section-head">
        <h2>Servings</h2>
        <span class="chev" aria-hidden="true">▸</span>
      </div>
      <p>Cooling is a small, private mobile app for two people.</p>
      <p>Either person can perform a single action called Chomp.</p>
      <p>A Chomp sends a quiet buzz to the other person. The notification contains no message, explanation, or instruction.</p>
      <p>A Chomp also places something in the oven for the sender for exactly 108 seconds.</p>
      <p>While something is in the oven, the app shows “in the oven • N seconds”. When the oven time ends, the app returns to “Cooling”.</p>
      <p>There is no chat.</p>
      <p>There are no replies.</p>
      <p>There is no obligation to respond.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="section tight" aria-label="Ingredients">
      <div class="section-head">
        <h2>Ingredients</h2>
        <span class="chev" aria-hidden="true">▸</span>
      </div>
      <p>Cooling never names what is in the oven. It may be affection, irritation, longing, attention, grief, or nothing in particular.</p>
      <p>Naming it would turn it into content.</p>
      <p>Measuring it would turn it into work.</p>
      <p>The app leaves it unspecified on purpose.</p>
      <p>Each person’s oven is independent. There is no turn-taking and no synchronization. It shows only one historical signal: “last chomp: just now / 12m ago / 3h ago / yesterday”.</p>
      <p>The app enforces restraint quietly and without reward.</p>
      <p>The oven time is finite and precise.</p>
      <p>Everything else is cooling.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="section tight" aria-label="Nutrition">
      <div class="section-head">
        <h2>Nutrition</h2>
        <span class="chev" aria-hidden="true">▸</span>
      </div>
      <p>Cooling deliberately avoids messaging threads, read receipts, presence indicators, analytics, streaks, reminders, and growth mechanics.</p>
      <p>These features convert care into labor and attention into performance.</p>
      <p>Cooling refuses that conversion.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="section tight" aria-label="Done">
      <div class="section-head">
        <h2>Done</h2>
        <span class="chev" aria-hidden="true">▸</span>
      </div>
      <p>Cooling is complete by design.</p>
      <p>It has no roadmap.</p>
      <p>It does not seek improvement through addition.</p>
      <p>There is no recipe.</p>
      <p>If it adds replies, metrics, optimization, or explanation, it should be considered broken.</p>
      <p>Cooling is everything besides putting something briefly in the oven.</p>
    </section>
  </main>
